s New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Income tax. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Bill contains provisions allowing Welsh G</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">overnment to hold a Referendum on devolution of income tax to Wales, and to vary it if devolution is approved in the Referendum. Significantly however it would not be without restriction as for example a cut in the top rate would automatically trigger a cu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t in the bottom rate and so on.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">RICS Wales position. We will decide on taking a position when a Referendum is called by Welsh Government and following Consultation and engagement with our Members and based on circumstances at that time.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Devolution of St</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">amp Duty Land Tax</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">RICS Wales position. We would comment that it could potentially allow Welsh Government to invest in Infrastructure, and that the effect would depend on what Welsh Government did with it. So if for exampl</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e it was used to reform the tiered</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> element, or to make Wales relatively more attractive this would likely be positive. Conversely however we would be very concerned if it was used to raise revenue over and above that levied in England because of the geographical proximity of Wales to Engla</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nd versus Scotland and the resulting cross border nature of many developers. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Devolution of Landfill Tax</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">RICS Wa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">les position. We welcome this provided</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> it is used to support investment in Infrastructure in Wales.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Borrowing limits for Welsh Government. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The Bill will allow Welsh Government borrowing powers of £500 million fo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">r Capital spending </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> £500 million on their current account. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">RICS Wales position. While we would not rule out supporting higher limits in future</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> we</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> think this is fine for now. How</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ever</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the caveat that it should be regularly reviewed to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reflect changing conditions and needs. However we warmly welcome the greater flexibility in regards to the circumstances in which Welsh Government Ministers can borrow in the short term</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Constitution</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">al Proposals</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The Bill will increase the Assembly Term to 5 years and drop the ban on dual list and constituency candidacies for the Welsh Assembly at the same election.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">RICS Wales position. We have decided to remain neutral on these</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> electoral</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> points. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Clause allowing devolution of more taxes without the need for primary legislation. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">RICS Wales position. In our view this is a sensible measure granting flexibility as devolution in Wales and the constitutional position across the UK continues to evolve go</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing forward.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Clause Allowing Welsh Government and UK Government to agree a protocol relating to the Law Commission’s work in Wales.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">RICS Wales position. We would strongly support this and ask Welsh Government and the UK Government to agree such a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">protoco</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">l as swiftly as they can to help ensure devolved legislation operates smoothly alongside UK wide legislation.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.05pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>